Communities in Mankweng, Ga-Mamabolo and high catchment areas in the city are likely to experience low pressure or a shortage of water due to power outage at Ebenezer plant since Tuesday evening.
Communications and Marketing Manager of Polokwane Municipality, Matshidiso Mothapo confirmed earlier today (Wednesday) that the municipality had received notification from Lepelle-Northern Water that the power supply at Ebenezer plant had been interrupted since Tuesday evening. He further said the matter was reported to the Tzaneen Municipality.
Mothapo indicated that the situation might affect all areas from Ga-Mamabolo, Mankweng and high catchment areas in the city. He advised residents to use water sparingly to avoid reservoirs being seriously affected.
Story: ENDY SENYATSI
